@startuml
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
' @ref(USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE)
'
' Objective-side runtime flow of the /mdd-deploy utility skill. Two
' phases: PLAN (SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE) writes the diagram + IaC + runbook,
' then EXECUTE (SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE) runs that runbook to live traffic.
'
' CHANGE (cycle 0021): the skill no longer stops after writing artifacts.
' The plan phase ends by handing off to a new execution phase that manages
' auth, dry-runs, applies, provisions, migrates, and routes traffic —
' pausing only at irreversible steps and halting on the first failed step.
'
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "PLAN phase. How /mdd-deploy turns a one-line description into a deployment plan: validate target=azure-container-apps, read MDD models + the target repo read-only, STOP for a blocking clarification on ambiguity OR a GENERALIZED go-live landmine, CONFIRM the IaC dialect AND the deployment purpose (dev/staging/prod; no silent default) before writing anything, run an ACCESS-COMPLETENESS pass over every secured store, write the deployment diagram, generate secure-by-default IaC in the confirmed dialect sized for the confirmed purpose, write the runbook — then HAND OFF to SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE to run it.")
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "How /mdd-render rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to its deterministic .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg mirror so the deployment diagram is inspectable like every other diagram. Additive, non-gating.")
' @desc(SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE, "EXECUTE phase. How /mdd-deploy runs the generated runbook to live traffic: it manages cloud auth (az login + selects/verifies the subscription, stopping on mismatch), validates the IaC and runs a DRY-RUN (terraform plan / az what-if) showing the diff, then walks the runbook via Bash (az/terraform/docker). Idempotent/reversible steps run autonomously; the executor BLOCKS for confirmation only at irreversible steps — one APPLY gate covering infra apply + secret writes + the pre-traffic migration job — then deploys the new revision at 0% traffic and health-checks it. The GO-LIVE gate surfaces the full production billing multi-factor state and BLOCKS before routing live traffic; it is never auto-confirmed. Execution HALTS on the first failed step. Realizes USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE + USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE; constrained by OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-*.")
title /mdd-deploy plan, execute, and inspection (objective)

actor "Operator" as Op
participant "/mdd-deploy\n(skill: plan + executor)" as Dep
participant ".mdd/models/\ncomponents + use-cases" as Models
participant "../atlas-ate-server\n(target repo, read-only)" as Target
database ".mdd/deploy/\nazure-container-apps/" as Store
participant "../atlas-ate-server/\ninfra/ (generated IaC)" as Infra
participant "Bash: az, terraform, docker" as CLI
participant "Azure subscription\n(LIVE)" as Az
participant "/mdd-render" as Render
database ".mdd/rendered/deploy/" as Rendered

== SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE (PLAN) ==
Op -> Dep : /mdd-deploy <deployment description>
alt target is not azure-container-apps
  Dep --> Op : not yet supported (v1 = azure-container-apps only); stop
else target is azure-container-apps
  Dep -> Models : read components + use-cases (the "what")
  Dep -> Target : read README, Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml,\n.env.example, src (READ-ONLY)
  opt ambiguity OR a GENERALIZED landmine (app-config, purpose, or access-path)
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING clarification (same discipline as /mdd-cycle);\nSURFACE the gap, never bury it as a runbook STOP note
    Op --> Dep : decision
  end

  group MANDATORY dialect confirmation, BEFORE any artifact (USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm: "generate <dialect> IaC?"\n(unspecified/unconfirmed -> STOP, write nothing)
    Op --> Dep : confirmed dialect
  end
  group MANDATORY deployment-purpose confirmation (USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE)
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm purpose + SURFACE purpose-appropriate\noptions (DB tier/redundancy, recommended doorway)
    Op --> Dep : confirmed purpose + choices
  end
  group ACCESS-COMPLETENESS pass, BEFORE any artifact (USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK)
    Dep -> Dep : name READER + WRITER for every secured store;\neach needs an identity and an admitted network path
    opt read-but-never-written, OR a writer with no admitted path
      Dep -> Op : BLOCKING: SURFACE the hole + connectivity options
      Op --> Dep : choice (never auto-decided by the skill)
    end
  end

  Dep -> Store : write diagram.puml + runbook.md
  alt confirmed dialect is Bicep
    Dep -> Infra : generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.bicep (+ modules)
  else confirmed dialect is Terraform
    Dep -> Infra : generate SECURE-BY-DEFAULT infra/main.tf (+ modules):\nazurerm provider + remote state backend
  end
  Dep -> Dep : HAND OFF to SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE (run the runbook)
end

== SEQ-DEPLOY-EXECUTE (RUN) ==
note over Dep
  Precondition: the PLAN phase produced diagram + IaC + runbook.
  The runbook is now the EXECUTION PLAN the skill walks itself.
end note
group AUTH — managed by the skill (USE-DEPLOY-EXECUTE)
  Dep -> CLI : az login (interactive device/browser)
  CLI --> Op : complete the auth handshake
  Op --> Dep : authenticated
  Dep -> CLI : az account set --subscription <target>
  opt wrong or ambiguous subscription
    Dep -> Op : BLOCKING: surface the subscription mismatch; STOP
  end
end
group PREFLIGHT — DRY-RUN before any apply (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-DRYRUN-BEFORE-APPLY)
  Dep -> CLI : validate IaC (terraform validate / az bicep build)
  Dep -> CLI : DRY-RUN (terraform plan / az deployment what-if)
  CLI --> Dep : plan diff
  Dep -> Op : show the diff
end
group EXECUTE — autonomous except irreversible; HALT on first error (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-HALT-ON-ERROR)
  Dep -> CLI : resource group + ACR create; docker build + push (idempotent, AUTONOMOUS)
  Dep -> Op : BLOCKING confirm — APPLY this plan?\n(one gate covering infra apply + secret writes + migration job)
  Op --> Dep : approve (OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-PAUSE-IRREVERSIBLE)
  Dep -> CLI : apply infra (terraform apply / az deployment create)
  CLI -> Az : provision Container Apps, ACR, Postgres, Key Vault, OpenAI
  Dep -> CLI : provision secrets (az keyvault secret set)
  CLI -> Az : write secrets into Key Vault
  Dep -> CLI : run migration job (completes BEFORE traffic)
  CLI -> Az : schema migrate
  Dep -> CLI : deploy new revision at 0% traffic; health-check
  opt any step failed
    Dep -> Op : HALT — report the failing step; run NO further step
  end
end
group GO-LIVE — never auto-confirmed (USE-DEPLOY-GOLIVE / OCL-DEPLOY-EXEC-GOLIVE-CONFIRMED)
  Dep -> Op : SURFACE full billing multi-factor gate state\n(ENABLE_PRODUCTION_BILLING, APP_ENV, DATABASE_MARKER,\nPUBLIC_HOST, APPLE_ENVIRONMENT, App Attest prod); BLOCKING confirm
  Op --> Dep : confirm go-live
  Dep -> CLI : route 100% traffic to the new revision (GO LIVE)
  CLI -> Az : live-traffic cutover
end
Dep -> CLI : verify ingress responds + revision healthy
Dep --> Op : report — deployed and LIVE, or HALTED at the failing step
note over Az
  New revision deploys at 0% traffic and is health-checked
  BEFORE the go-live cutover, so a bad rollout cannot take
  down the running revision. The billing gate is never
  auto-flipped — GO-LIVE is the one stop full-auto never skips.
end note

== SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT ==
Op -> Render : /mdd-render
Render -> Store : read .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml
Render -> Rendered : write .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg\n(deterministic mirror; additive, non-gating)
Render --> Op : rendered SVG list

note over Store
  .mdd/deploy/ is an inspection artifact only.
  /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the /mdd-cycle
  parity loop never read it.
end note
@enduml
